cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.CR

The paper deals with session behaviors in client/server systems, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of formal methods and software engineering. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a likely category. The paper also discusses decidability, which is a topic in logic and computation, making cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) another likely category. The paper also mentions the need for a tighter analysis of client/server interactions, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses compliance and sub-behavior relations, which are topics in programming languages, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with the security of client/server systems, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
